            <fr:title text="Formally real">Formally real</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
              <fr:link href="/hall-2024-sandwich/" title="Sandwich operators and Einstein deformations of compact symmetric spaces related to Jordan algebras" uri="http://localhost:8000/hall-2024-sandwich/" display-uri="hall-2024-sandwich" type="local">[hall-2024-sandwich]</fr:link>
            </fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A Jordan algebra <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(J,\circ )]]></fr:tex> is called <html:dfn>formally real</html:dfn> whenever for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\in \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> and for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x_{1},…,x_{n}\in  J]]></fr:tex>, we have:</html:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[x_{1}^{2}+\cdots +x_{n}^{2}=0\quad \hbox {implies}\quad  x_{1}=\cdots =x_{n}=0]]></fr:tex>
            <html:p>Observe <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(\mathbb {R},\circ )]]></fr:tex> is formally real.</html:p>
            <html:p>We can decompose formally real Jordan algebras into the direct sum of <fr:link href="/jordan-0005/" title="Simple Jordan algebra" uri="http://localhost:8000/jordan-0005/" display-uri="jordan-0005" type="local">simple</fr:link> Jordan algebras.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
